author: rjung
msg: Supporting "+" and "-" syntax in SSLProtocol configuration
(OpenSSL).
This allows settings like "all-TLSv1" (or if you
prefer "all-TLSv1"). The list is always
build starting with an empty list, even if the
first token has a "+" prefix.
This is similar to the mod_ssl behavior. It differs
in the handling of a token without "+" or "-" which
we don't support except for the first token that initializes
the list.
r1682028 and r1682033 from trunk resp. r1682034,
